{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}
The [[New Zealand National Party]]'s '''Senior Whip''' administers the “[[Whip (politics)|whipping in]]” system that tries to ensure that party MPs attend and vote according to the party leadership's wishes.

The party's current senior whip is [[Jami-Lee Ross]], who sits for the [[Botany (New Zealand electorate)|Botany electorate]], elected May 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.national.org.nz/national_s_new_whips_announced|title=National’s new whips announced|work=NZ National Party|access-date=23 October 2017|language=en}}</ref> The junior whip is [[Barbara Kuriger]] ([[Member of parliament|MP]] for [[Taranaki-King Country]]) and third whip is [[Tim van de Molen]] (MP for [[Waikato (New Zealand electorate)|Waikato]]).

